org.semanticweb.rulewerk.core.reasoner

Interface QueryAnswerCount

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    QueryAnswerCountImpl

    public interface QueryAnswerCount
    Container for correctness and number of query answers, i.e. the number of facts that the query maps to. Depending on the state of the reasoning (materialisation) and its KnowledgeBase, the answers can have a different Correctness
    • If Correctness.SOUND_AND_COMPLETE, materialisation over current knowledge base has completed, and the query answers are guaranteed to be correct.
    • If Correctness.SOUND_BUT_INCOMPLETE, the results are guaranteed to be sound, but may be incomplete. This can happen
      • when materialisation has not completed (Reasoner.reason() returns false),
      • or when the knowledge base was modified after reasoning, and the materialisation does not reflect the current knowledge base. Re-materialisation (Reasoner.reason()) is required in order to obtain complete query answers with respect to the current knowledge base.
    • If Correctness.INCORRECT, the results may be incomplete, and some results may be unsound. This can happen when the knowledge base was modified and the reasoner materialisation is no longer consistent with the current knowledge base. Re-materialisation (Reasoner.reason()) is required, in order to obtain correct query answers.
